<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="366" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,1328,1460]" pageId="11" pageNumber="366">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fall" authorityYear="1922" box="[140,325,1329,1355]" class="Insecta" family="Gyrinidae" genus="Gyrinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="366" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugionis">
<emphasis box="[140,325,1329,1355]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="366">Gyrinus pugionis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[563,747,1328,1355]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="11" pageNumber="366">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[811,950,1328,1355]" country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="11" pageNumber="366">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Roughley RE" pageId="11" pageNumber="366" pagination="72 - 673" refId="ref7727" refString="Roughley RE (1991) Family Gyrinidae: Whirligig Beetles. In: Bousquet Y (Ed) Checklist of Beetles of Canada and Alaska. Ottawa, Ontario: Agriculture Canada, publication 1861 / E: pp. 72 - 673. http: // www. canacoll. org / Coleo / Checklist / PDF files / GYRINIDAE. pdf [accessed 29 June 2009]" type="journal article" year="1991">Roughley (1991)</bibRefCitation>
(Fig. 11). 
<bibRefCitation author="Robert A" box="[335,496,1363,1390]" pageId="11" pageNumber="366" pagination="67 - 78" refId="ref7670" refString="Robert A (1955) Les associations de Gyrins dans les etangs et les lacs du Parc du Mont Tremblant. The Canadian Entomologist 87: 67 - 78." type="journal article" year="1955">Robert (1955)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Morrissette R" box="[552,762,1363,1390]" pageId="11" pageNumber="366" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref7605" refString="Morrissette R (1979) Les coleopteres Gyrinidae du Quebec. Cordulia, Supplement 8: 1 - 43." type="journal article" year="1979">Morrissette (1979)</bibRefCitation>
both reported it from peaty or semi-peaty lakes, 
<bibRefCitation author="Robert A" box="[332,492,1398,1425]" pageId="11" pageNumber="366" pagination="67 - 78" refId="ref7670" refString="Robert A (1955) Les associations de Gyrins dans les etangs et les lacs du Parc du Mont Tremblant. The Canadian Entomologist 87: 67 - 78." type="journal article" year="1955">Robert (1955)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that it invades narrow outflow streams from such lakes. 
<bibRefCitation author="Oygur S &amp; Wolfe GW" box="[266,546,1434,1460]" pageId="11" pageNumber="366" pagination="1 - 97" refId="ref7625" refString="Oygur S, Wolfe GW (1991) Classification, distribution and phylogeny of North American (north of Mexico) species of Gyrinus Muller (Coleoptera: Gyrinidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 207: 1 - 97." type="journal article" year="1991">Oygur and Wolfe (1991)</bibRefCitation>
reported it primarily (88%) from lentic habitats.
</paragraph>
